00:31:34,060 --> 00:31:38,060
 Delay in flying your flag could lead to potential compromise.

552
00:31:38,060 --> 00:31:41,060
 And then the realization, "Oh, someone's trying to..."

553
00:31:41,060 --> 00:31:43,060
 "Oh, I didn't realize you were one of them."

554
00:31:43,060 --> 00:31:47,060
 So fly your flag early.

555
00:31:47,060 --> 00:31:49,060
 Secondly, make a connection.

556
00:31:49,060 --> 00:31:50,060
 Find common ground.

557
00:31:50,060 --> 00:31:53,060
 People like to talk about things that they are interested in.

558
00:31:53,060 --> 00:31:58,060
 If we show an interest in the things they're interested in,

559
00:31:58,060 --> 00:32:00,060
 they might be more interested in what we have to say.

560
00:32:02,060 --> 00:32:05,060
 When I was in sales, the first thing I'd do is go to someone's office.

561
00:32:05,060 --> 00:32:09,060
 I'd look at the books, the bookshelf, all the stuff around

562
00:32:09,060 --> 00:32:12,060
 for clues on things they're interested in.

563
00:32:12,060 --> 00:32:16,060
 People like to talk about their hobbies, like Pickable.

564
00:32:16,060 --> 00:32:19,060
 And they want to talk about their families.

565
00:32:19,060 --> 00:32:24,060
 Invite them out for a coffee, or better still, happy hour.

566
00:32:24,060 --> 00:32:28,060
 To get to know them.

567
00:32:28,060 --> 00:32:33,060
 Get to know them rather than WhatsAppping them the latest church invitation.

568
00:32:33,060 --> 00:32:42,060
 I'd like to go on, but I want to emphasize, thirdly, look for opportunities.

569
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:46,060
 The Holy Spirit will give you windows.

570
00:32:46,060 --> 00:32:55,060
 25 years ago, one of my team at work knocked at my door to ask me a question.

571
00:32:55,060 --> 00:32:56,060
 She was thinking of leaving.

572
00:32:56,060 --> 00:32:58,060
 I didn't know.

573
00:32:58,060 --> 00:33:01,060
 She said, "How? How come?

574
00:33:01,060 --> 00:33:05,060
 How have you been able to stay with one company for 25 years?"

575
00:33:05,060 --> 00:33:09,060
 I gave an answer I would not normally recommend.

576
00:33:09,060 --> 00:33:13,060
 I just said, "Jesus."

577
00:33:13,060 --> 00:33:17,060
 But that prompted an hour conversation.

578
00:33:17,060 --> 00:33:20,060
 At the end of it, she prayed a prayer to receive Christ,

579
00:33:20,060 --> 00:33:22,060
 and I prayed for her to be filled with the Spirit.

580
00:33:22,060 --> 00:33:24,060
 She came to the Vine.

581
00:33:25,060 --> 00:33:27,060
 We were in the Regal Hotel at the time.

582
00:33:27,060 --> 00:33:30,060
 She's still very much part of the Vine.

583
00:33:30,060 --> 00:33:32,060
 She was at 9.15 this morning.

584
00:33:32,060 --> 00:33:38,060
 I baptized her in Repulse Bay, married her and her husband in Union Church,

585
00:33:38,060 --> 00:33:41,060
 and dedicated their son also in the Vine.

586
00:33:41,060 --> 00:33:44,060
 That's my window.

587
00:33:44,060 --> 00:33:47,060
 Your window might look different,

588
00:33:47,060 --> 00:33:53,060
 but what I want you to do is to encourage you to be ready when those doors open,

589
00:33:53,060 --> 00:33:56,060
 which leads to my fourth tip.

590
00:33:56,060 --> 00:33:59,060
 Fourthly, know your story.

591
00:33:59,060 --> 00:34:04,060
 No story is better than yours.

592
00:34:04,060 --> 00:34:08,060
 People can argue about theology.

593
00:34:08,060 --> 00:34:10,060
 In fact, they often do.

594
00:34:10,060 --> 00:34:15,060
 But they cannot argue about your personal experience.

595
00:34:15,060 --> 00:34:21,060
 What I was like before I met Christ.

596
00:34:22,060 --> 00:34:24,060
 How I met Christ.

597
00:34:24,060 --> 00:34:29,060
 What difference has He made to my life?

598
00:34:29,060 --> 00:34:36,060
 In mission team preparation, we try and do this in one minute,

599
00:34:36,060 --> 00:34:40,060
 a one-minute testimony, because you may only get a minute.

600
00:34:40,060 --> 00:34:42,060
 You might get longer.

601
00:34:42,060 --> 00:34:43,060
 You may only get a minute.

602
00:34:43,060 --> 00:34:49,060
 So find someone this week and practice your one-minute testimony with them.

603
00:34:49,060 --> 00:34:54,060
 What I was like before, how I met Christ, and what my life has been like since.

604
00:34:54,060 --> 00:35:00,060
 As I said earlier, your story is maybe the first time

605
00:35:00,060 --> 00:35:04,060
 someone has opened up biblical truth to them.

606
00:35:04,060 --> 00:35:09,060
 Everyone deserves the opportunity to hear.

607
00:35:09,060 --> 00:35:13,060
 Just be open to being that opportunity.

608
00:35:13,060 --> 00:35:17,060
 And you are not responsible for their response.

609
00:35:18,060 --> 00:35:20,060
 Indeed, it may come years later.

610
00:35:20,060 --> 00:35:25,060
 Earlier this year, I heard about two former colleagues from the '90s

611
00:35:25,060 --> 00:35:27,060
 recently coming to faith.

612
00:35:27,060 --> 00:35:32,060
 And in the last month, three of our Pickleball group have accepted Christ.

613
00:35:32,060 --> 00:35:37,060
 Lastly, let your actions speak.

614
00:35:37,060 --> 00:35:40,060
 Sometimes we don't need to say anything.

615
00:35:40,060 --> 00:35:44,060
 The popular idiom is "actions speak louder than words."

616
00:35:44,060 --> 00:35:48,060
 There is a danger when our words and our actions don't match up.

617
00:35:48,060 --> 00:35:50,060
 Consistency is the key.

618
00:35:50,060 --> 00:35:56,060
 The reality of our social media-driven age where what people are saying

619
00:35:56,060 --> 00:36:02,060
 seems to have a big impact, and oftentimes, it is those who are keyboard warriors

620
00:36:02,060 --> 00:36:06,060
 who are shaping the narrative of our cities and culture.

621
00:36:06,060 --> 00:36:10,060
 I think there is a good reminder here for all of us

622
00:36:10,060 --> 00:36:14,060
 to live less online and more in the real world.

623
00:36:14,060 --> 00:36:18,060
 To be more a Christian in our everyday moments

624
00:36:18,060 --> 00:36:21,060
 than be pretending to be one online.

625
00:36:21,060 --> 00:36:25,060
 There is a common expression, "Going the extra mile."

626
00:36:25,060 --> 00:36:28,060
 It's found in Matthew 5:41.

627
00:36:28,060 --> 00:36:35,060
 We can be the extra mile people in our workplace.

628
00:36:37,060 --> 00:36:41,060
 Loving people is important.

629
00:36:41,060 --> 00:36:48,060
 Loving people is important regardless of whether they end up saying the sinner's prayer or not.

630
00:36:48,060 --> 00:36:56,060
 We are commanded to love people regardless of the surface result.

631
00:36:56,060 --> 00:37:04,060
 Can I ask, as I conclude, that we as a church, and we prayed it earlier,

632
00:37:04,060 --> 00:37:09,060
 that we resolve to take hold of this opportunity

633
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:15,060
 to set sail for those uncharted territories.

634
00:37:15,060 --> 00:37:19,060
 I want to have the opportunity to pray for you all.

635
00:37:19,060 --> 00:37:22,060
 I particularly want to pray for three groups today.

636
00:37:22,060 --> 00:37:27,060
 Firstly, younger adults. I see a few of you out there are quite young

637
00:37:27,060 --> 00:37:29,060
 who are wondering what's next.

638
00:37:29,060 --> 00:37:33,060
 This sense of calling, it's very difficult to take it.

639
00:37:33,060 --> 00:37:36,060
 What's next? What's next? We want to pray for you.

640
00:37:36,060 --> 00:37:42,060
 Secondly, for those who are older but thinking about a career change.

641
00:37:42,060 --> 00:37:46,060
 And thirdly, I know there are a lot of people in this category,

642
00:37:46,060 --> 00:37:49,060
 people who are currently without a job.

643
00:37:49,060 --> 00:37:55,060
 If you're in these groups, we pray that God will help you see the big picture.

644
00:37:56,060 --> 00:38:01,060
 And I do realize that there are practical, obvious practical considerations

645
00:38:01,060 --> 00:38:03,060
 which I'm not taking lightly.

646
00:38:03,060 --> 00:38:07,060
 But I want to encourage you to build a cathedral,

647
00:38:07,060 --> 00:38:11,060
 not just a wall or a row of bricks.

648
00:38:11,060 --> 00:38:15,060
 As a church, we want to bless you,

649
00:38:15,060 --> 00:38:19,060
 especially if you're in one of these groups.

650
00:38:19,060 --> 00:38:23,060
 Can we all stand and ask the band to come back?

651
00:38:24,060 --> 00:38:27,060
 (Band playing)

652
00:38:27,060 --> 00:38:33,060
 Let's have a moment of quiet, just reflect on what we've heard.

653
00:38:33,060 --> 00:38:42,060
 This afternoon, I want to invite you to an ordination service.

654
00:38:42,060 --> 00:38:45,060
 You're all going to be ordained

655
00:38:45,060 --> 00:38:48,060
 as pastors in your field.

656
00:38:48,060 --> 00:38:52,060
 I'm going to pray for you, for the Holy Spirit.

657
00:38:53,060 --> 00:38:55,060
 Just to come.

658
00:38:55,060 --> 00:39:00,060
 If you're comfortable, just stretch your hands out in front of you.

659
00:39:00,060 --> 00:39:04,060
 Holy Spirit, you're already here.

660
00:39:04,060 --> 00:39:09,060
 You've been here all day, moving in our midst.

661
00:39:09,060 --> 00:39:14,060
 But we invite you to come to us now, Lord,

662
00:39:14,060 --> 00:39:20,060
 and anoint us, empower us,

663
00:39:21,060 --> 00:39:26,060
 ordain us as your ministers in the marketplace,

664
00:39:26,060 --> 00:39:34,060
